WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.020 --> 00:00:02.550
- The biggest things we achieve at work

2
00:00:02.550 --> 00:00:04.260
often start as an idea.

3
00:00:04.260 --> 00:00:06.660
But the journey from
a spark of inspiration

4
00:00:06.660 --> 00:00:09.240
to a finished project isn't easy.

5
00:00:09.240 --> 00:00:11.760
Identifying the right
solution, building a plan,

6
00:00:11.760 --> 00:00:14.280
and, you know, managing all
the bumps along the way?

7
00:00:14.280 --> 00:00:16.140
That can feel like a lot.

8
00:00:16.140 --> 00:00:19.320
But what if you had a new
partner in this process?

9
00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:22.680
A creative collaborator to help
you generate possibilities,

10
00:00:22.680 --> 00:00:25.560
a master strategist to
stress test your assumptions,

11
00:00:25.560 --> 00:00:27.180
and an execution expert

12
00:00:27.180 --> 00:00:30.840
to build a plan based on your
ideas to get the job done?

13
00:00:30.840 --> 00:00:32.760
Hi, my name is Yul.

14
00:00:32.760 --> 00:00:34.560
I'm a VPO of Product Management at Google,

15
00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:36.240
and I help lead a research team

16
00:00:36.240 --> 00:00:37.920
called Paradigms of Intelligence,

17
00:00:37.920 --> 00:00:39.120
which tries to understand

18
00:00:39.120 --> 00:00:41.550
the nature and building
blocks of intelligence.

19
00:00:41.550 --> 00:00:44.430
Now, in this course, we'll
show you how Gemini can be

20
00:00:44.430 --> 00:00:46.080
that creative partner for you

21
00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:49.410
so that you can think big and
achieve your goals at work.

22
00:00:49.410 --> 00:00:52.860
First, you'll learn techniques
to generate ideas with you.

23
00:00:52.860 --> 00:00:55.560
We'll simulate experts and
push creative boundaries

24
00:00:55.560 --> 00:00:58.410
to uncover solutions you
never would've considered.

25
00:00:58.410 --> 00:01:00.150
And we'll show you how you can use Gemini

26
00:01:00.150 --> 00:01:03.540
to bring industry knowledge
into the process to help.

27
00:01:03.540 --> 00:01:06.450
Next, you'll pressure test solutions.

28
00:01:06.450 --> 00:01:08.010
Now, the best ideas are ones

29
00:01:08.010 --> 00:01:10.800
that can stand up to potential
problems in the future.

30
00:01:10.800 --> 00:01:14.640
But spotting those problems
before they happen can be tough.

31
00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:17.190
You'll learn to use Gemini
as a devil's advocate

32
00:01:17.190 --> 00:01:21.510
to find risks in your strategy
before they become problems.

33
00:01:21.510 --> 00:01:23.010
You'll also learn how to apply constraints

34
00:01:23.010 --> 00:01:24.780
to get to the most relevant solutions

35
00:01:24.780 --> 00:01:27.240
so that you can choose the best path.

36
00:01:27.240 --> 00:01:29.100
Finally, you'll manage your project

37
00:01:29.100 --> 00:01:31.500
by getting everyone on the same page.

38
00:01:31.500 --> 00:01:33.180
We'll show you how to use NotebookLM

39
00:01:33.180 --> 00:01:34.860
to create an information hub

40
00:01:34.860 --> 00:01:36.540
where you and your
teammates can ask questions

41
00:01:36.540 --> 00:01:39.840
and get answers about the
project in literally seconds.

42
00:01:39.840 --> 00:01:41.550
It all sounds pretty great, right?

43
00:01:41.550 --> 00:01:43.290
Well, it kind of is.

44
00:01:43.290 --> 00:01:44.640
But to make this a reality,

45
00:01:44.640 --> 00:01:46.890
you'll also need to
understand some key principles

46
00:01:46.890 --> 00:01:48.870
for using AI effectively.

47
00:01:48.870 --> 00:01:51.390
But, don't worry, we've got you covered.

48
00:01:51.390 --> 00:01:53.910
First up is problem framing.

49
00:01:53.910 --> 00:01:56.460
Before you even consider using AI,

50
00:01:56.460 --> 00:01:57.660
you need to clearly define

51
00:01:57.660 --> 00:01:59.940
the problem you're
trying to solve and why.

52
00:01:59.940 --> 00:02:01.680
Where you are and where you want to go

53
00:02:01.680 --> 00:02:04.173
will anchor the process
from start to finish.

54
00:02:05.190 --> 00:02:07.740
You also provide essential context.

55
00:02:07.740 --> 00:02:09.780
Now, AI doesn't have all
the background information

56
00:02:09.780 --> 00:02:12.480
about your customers, your team dynamics,

57
00:02:12.480 --> 00:02:14.400
or your leadership's priorities.

58
00:02:14.400 --> 00:02:15.870
Those are the critical things

59
00:02:15.870 --> 00:02:17.730
that determine which solutions to pursue

60
00:02:17.730 --> 00:02:20.010
and what steps should be
added to your project plan.

61
00:02:20.010 --> 00:02:22.920
And that information
can only come from you.

62
00:02:22.920 --> 00:02:23.970
Throughout this process,

63
00:02:23.970 --> 00:02:26.610
you're setting up the problem,
exploring the options,

64
00:02:26.610 --> 00:02:27.690
and using your judgment

65
00:02:27.690 --> 00:02:30.390
to make a decision on what to do next.

66
00:02:30.390 --> 00:02:32.070
Now, AI isn't perfect,

67
00:02:32.070 --> 00:02:33.900
and it can sometimes give you ideas

68
00:02:33.900 --> 00:02:35.100
that won't be a good fit.

69
00:02:35.100 --> 00:02:37.710
So, please, be a tough critic.

70
00:02:37.710 --> 00:02:38.910
With this new way of working,

71
00:02:38.910 --> 00:02:40.200
you'll have a resource to turn to

72
00:02:40.200 --> 00:02:42.780
at almost every stage of
the project lifecycle,

73
00:02:42.780 --> 00:02:44.880
from idea to plan to delivery.

74
00:02:44.880 --> 00:02:46.530
It's a mindset shift.

75
00:02:46.530 --> 00:02:47.820
And, by the end of this course,

76
00:02:47.820 --> 00:02:49.800
you'll be able to break
through creative blocks,

77
00:02:49.800 --> 00:02:53.130
find unexpected solutions
to complicated problems,

78
00:02:53.130 --> 00:02:55.380
and turn your best ideas into action plans

79
00:02:55.380 --> 00:02:56.760
that drive progress.

80
00:02:56.760 --> 00:02:57.593
So good luck.